    "benefits": "Niacin is known for its cholesterol-lowering effects, as it can help increase HDL (good) cholesterol while decreasing LDL (bad) cholesterol and triglycerides. It may also improve circulation, reduce inflammation, and support brain health by aiding in the production of neurotransmitters. Furthermore, niacin is often used to manage conditions like pellagra (niacin deficiency), and to alleviate symptoms of certain skin disorders.",
